<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="objectType">Wall</rs> of  doorway to stage room.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><w>Inscribed</w> at <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">1.40</measure> above ground; cut on a rough surface.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Irregular, lunate, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.05-0.07</measure>. There are slight traces of further letters on this wall.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0001" notAfter="0600">First  to sixth century A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">context</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab>
<lb n="1"/>
<persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Φιλιστίων">Φιλιστίωνος</name></persName> 
<lb n="2"/>
<w lemma="διασκεῦος">διασκεύη</w></ab>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Equipment of Philistion.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of the group of inscriptions, apparently by performers, at the doorways of the rooms on the stage front:  <xref type="inscription" n="698" href="080008">8.8</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="699" href="080009">8.9</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="700" href="080104">8.104</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1567" href="080015">8.15</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1707" href="080016">8.16</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1716" href="080017">8.17</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1754" href="080018">8.18</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1755" href="080019">8.19</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1759" href="080020">8.20</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1760" href="080021">8.21</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="1895" href="080022">8.22</xref>. See <bibl n="PPA">Roueché, <title>PPA</title>, pp. 15-25.</bibl>.</p>

</div>
